article.headline: Norfolk St. 87, Coppin St. 77
article.story: BALTIMORE, Md. -- Michael Deloach scored 24 points to lead Norfolk State to an 87-77 win over Coppin State on Saturday. Deloach shot 10-for-15 from the field for the Spartans (3-10, 1-1 Mideastern Atlantic Conference). Corey Lyons had 20 points, and Kyle O'Quinn added 10 points and 12 rebounds. The Eagles (2-13, 0-2) were paced by Tywain McKee, who scored 27 points. Sam Coleman contrubited 18 points, six rebounds and two blocks. Norfolk State outrebounded Coppin State 39-30. They also blocked seven shots as a team, and totaled 16 team assists. The Spartans received 18 points off fast breaks, and shot 64.2 percent from the field (34-for-53). The Eagles shot 36.1 percent (22-for-61).
